This paper deals with mitigating side-channel attacks, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The approach presented in the paper involves managing memory pages, which is a task typically handled by operating systems (cs.OS). The paper also mentions container boundaries, which suggests a focus on virtualization and cloud computing (cs.AR). Additionally, the paper involves formal verification and empirical evaluation, which are common in the areas of distributed computing (cs.DC) and software engineering (cs.SE).
